  "text": "Social tourism is also linked to debates in sustainable tourism due to the fact it takes a more holistic approach relating to the ethics underpinning sustainable tourism, and for the ways in which it is framed as a more responsible form of tourism [CITATION_1] , contrasted with the more morally circumspect practices of the global tourism industry. For example, HigginsDesbiolles (2006) argued that some forms of tourism, including social tourism can be considered more socially oriented since they are not profit driven; and thus more likely to consider the environment and local residents' views more favourably than the industry, often characterised by short-term, profit-driven interests. These characteristics are intrinsic to sustainable tourism values.",
